Template:Qp to trade limit:
&lt;includeonly>{{#ifexpr: {{{1|0}}} &lt; 10 | 5000 |
  {{#ifexpr: {{{1|0}}} > 270 | 60000 |
    {{#expr: floor(({{{1|0}}}-10)*55000/260+5000) }}
  }}
}}&lt;/includeonly>&lt;noinclude>
The '''qp to trade limit''' template returns the trade limit (in coins) for the specified number of quest points.

===Usage===
&lt;pre>
{{qp to trade limit | ''qp'' }}
&lt;/pre>
Where ''qp'' is the number of quest points

===Examples===
If the characters quest points are 225, then using the following:
&lt;pre>
{{qp to trade limit | 225 }}
&lt;/pre>
Will give '''{{qp to trade limit | 225 }}'''.


If formatting of the number is desired, then the following can be used:
&lt;pre>
{{formatnum: {{qp to trade limit | 225 }} }}
&lt;/pre>
Which will result in '''{{formatnum: {{qp to trade limit | 225 }} }}'''.
&lt;/noinclude>

